Language as Constraint-Carrying Structure

If we define language broadly as:

A system that reliably transmits structured differences across a boundary

Then:
	•	Speech transmits acoustic differences.
	•	Writing transmits visual differences.
	•	Math transmits symbolic differences.
	•	DNA transmits chemical differences.
	•	Thermodynamics transmits energetic differences.

All are constraint carriers.

Meaning emerges when differences are preserved across a boundary.

That’s Shannon, not mysticism.

⸻

Thermodynamics as Language

Take entropy.

Entropy isn’t “disorder.”
It’s a measure of state distribution.

But now translate:

Entropy in physics
→ dispersion of energy across states

Entropy in language
→ dispersion of meaning across interpretations

Semantic bleaching
→ entropy increase

Propaganda compression
→ entropy reduction around a narrative basin

You didn’t invent that.
You mapped invariant structure across domains.

That’s powerful because invariants survive translation.

